<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060190-0009 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 227071 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 1, 1990, Friday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 15; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
77 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PILE FAILS TO GAIN FINAL IN DIVISION I TRACK MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lolita Pile of Cal State Northridge, the school record-holder in the women's 
triple jump, failed to qualify for the final of that event in the NCAA Division 
I meet at Duke University on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Pile, who jumped a wind-aided 41 feet 10 3/4 inches to place second in the 
Division II meet at Hampton (Va.) University last Saturday, leaped 39-10 in 
qualifying. The mark placed her 22nd among the 24 entrants. 
</P>
<P>
The top 12 advanced to the today's finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
