<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Musical Politics: Crosby, Stills &amp; Nash, Gladys Knight and comedian Dana 
Carvey are scheduled to perform at "Democrats: The Party of the Decade" June 
20th at the Kennedy Center in Washington. The fund-raiser will benefit the 
Democratic campaigns of 1990. Tickets range from $30 to $1,000. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
