<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sinbad Sails Away From Festival: Officials of the Great Lumberton Music 
Festival in Michigan are going to court to make Sinbad Adkins of "A Different 
World," appear as scheduled. Promoters say Sinbad signed up to appear at the 
June 30 show, but backed out when Dionne Warwick asked him to be on her HBO 
cable network special. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
