<P>
MEMBERS SOUGHT FOR ELECTION PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Simi Valley is seeking two regular and three alternate members to 
serve on the Citizens Election Advisory Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Registered voters who live in the city and are not involved in upcoming 
elections may apply for the posts. 
</P>
<P>
The five-member board reviews candidate and committee financial statements and 
helps city staff members identify any problems with campaign financial 
disclosure statements. 
</P>
<P>
Commission members also help prepare orientation briefings, informing 
candidates and campaign committees of state election requirements. 
</P>
<P>
Applications may be obtained from the city clerk's office at City Hall, 2929 
Tapo Canyon Road. The application deadline is July 6. JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</TEXT>
