<P>
QUAKE BRINGS REWARD FOR CHINA PRISONERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has shortened the sentences of 116 prisoners at a labor camp in western 
Qinghai province for good behavior during an earthquake last April that knocked 
down a camp wall and opened their way to freedom, an official newspaper said. 
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai newspaper Wen Hui Bao said 52 of the prisoners had already gained 
their freedom as a reward for not fleeing or for helping to rescue people 
trapped in rubble nearby by the magnitude 6.9 quake that killed 126 people. 
</P>
