<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: VALLEY CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Valley Center teen-ager died Thursday when her car hit a tree along a rural 
road. 
</P>
<P>
Marcia Ann Logue, 17, was driving west on Woods Valley Road near Lake Wohlford 
Road at 7:20 a.m. when her car left the road on a sharp curve and hit an oak, 
said California Highway Patrol Officer Jerry Bohrer. 
</P>
<P>
Logue, who lived near the accident site and traveled the road frequently, was 
apparently driving too fast to safely handle the curve, he said. She died at 
the scene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
