<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
MEESE'S BROTHER FAILS TO WIN PANEL'S OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Meese, brother of former U.S. Atty. Gen. Edwin Meese, failed to win 
confirmation to another four-year term on the state Unemployment Insurance 
Appeals Board, but the state Senate Rules Committee said it would again take up 
his reappointment at an unspecified date. Meese's continued service in his 
$86,000-a-year post was opposed by the California Labor Federation, AFL-CIO, 
which complained that the number of board decisions favoring unemployed 
laborers has dropped dramatically since Gov. George Deukmejian appointed Meese 
in 1985. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
