<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
VAN DE KAMP DETAILS AUTO RATE ROLLBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Atty. Gen. John K. Van de Kamp laid out a schedule of auto insurance rate 
rollbacks he said should be implemented under Proposition 103 and assailed 
Republican Insurance Commissioner Roxani Gillespie for failing to order such 
rollbacks. By his calculations, he said, two-car families with good driving 
records should get back an average of $472 in Los Angeles, $304 in San 
Bernardino and Riverside, $269 in San Diego, $338 in San Francisco, $268 in 
Sacramento. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
