<TEXT>
<P>
The University of Arkansas at Pine Bluff has been asked to explain 76 
allegations lodged against the school's football program by college football 
coaches, according to a Pine Bluff newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
The allegations involved player eligibility, playing non-registered players and 
improper transfers of students from other schools. The article said the 
complaints were lodged by coaches, both in and out of the Arkansas 
Intercollegiate Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Archie Cooley, UAPB head football coach and athletic director, denied the 
allegations. 
