<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BASEBALL FINALS; 
</P>
<P>
SMALL SCHOOLS, 1-A START TWO-DAY CHAMPIONSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Southern Section baseball championships will begin today with the title 
games for Small Schools and the 1-A Division at Blair Field in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The four other divisional finals will be played Saturday at Anaheim Stadium, 
beginning at 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
In today's first game, Boron (22-4) meets Rosamond (24-2) at 4:30 p.m. for the 
Small Schools title. 
</P>
<P>
Boron defeated Pasadena Poly, 20-10, and Rosamond beat Norwalk Leffingwell 
Christian, 7-2, in the semifinals. In the 1-A Division final at 7:30 p.m., Van 
Nuys Montclair Prep (24-3) faces Sun Valley Village Christian (18-6). 
</P>
<P>
Saturday, in the 5-A Division final, Huntington Beach Marina (16-12-1) plays 
Diamond Bar (21-8) at 7:30 p.m. In the semifinals, Marina downed top-seeded 
Westlake, 4-1, and Diamond Bar beat West Covina, 8-6, with two runs in the top 
of the seventh inning. 
</P>
<P>
San Luis Obispo (23-4) takes on West Covina South Hills (24-5) in the 4-A 
Division final at 4:30 p.m. San Luis Obispo edged Upland, 4-3, and South Hills 
blanked Fullerton Troy, 8-0, to reach the title game. 
</P>
<P>
Two heavy-hitting teams are in the 3-A Division final at 1 p.m. -- Tustin 
(26-3) and Whittier La Serna (27-5). In the semifinals, Tustin pounded 
Hesperia, 14-5, and La Serna routed Orange, 10-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the 2-A Division final at 10 a.m., El Segundo (27-3) plays San Marino 
(22-2-1). El Segundo defeated Camino Real League rival Long Beach St. Anthony, 
7-1, and San Marino beat Yucaipa, 2-1, in the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
