<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO REAL WINS ANOTHER SOFTBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For all intents and purposes, El Camino Real High needed only two innings 
Thursday to claim its third consecutive City Section 4-A Division softball 
title and seventh in the past eight years. 
</P>
<P>
The Conquistadores scored twice in each of the first two innings en route to an 
8-3 victory over West Valley League rival Chatsworth at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Alisha Knopf had two hits and two runs batted in and Jenny Fleming added three 
singles and an RBI for El Camino Real (23-3). Chatsworth finished at 13-6. 
</P>
<P>
Southern Section softball titles in five divisions will be settled this weekend 
at Mayfair Park in Long Beach. Friday in the 2-A Division, top-seeded Santa Fe 
plays Hesperia at 6 p.m. followed by Garden Grove vs. Charter Oak in the 4-A 
title game at 8. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday's games begin at 10 a.m. with the Small Schools Division game between 
Templeton and Maricopa. Agoura and Paraclete play for the 1-A title at 2:30 
p.m., followed by the 3-A final between El Toro and Don Lugo at 5:30 p.m. 
Top-seeded Marina meets Newbury Park in the 5-A game at 8 p.m. MIKE GLAZE 
</P>
</TEXT>
