<P>
There will be a free public screening today at 4 p.m. of the Czech 
feature-length documentary, "Pictures of the Old World," by Dusan Hanak, at 
USC's Norris Auditorium. Acclaimed at its recent AFI Fest screening, this 
portrait of indomitable, elderly villagers, living in virtually medieval 
conditions yet somehow preserving their humor, energy and optimism, was made in 
1973 but not released until 1989. 
