<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
ASSISTANT SUPT. TO LEAVE THIS MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ronald G. Bennett, an assistant superintendent for the Fullerton School 
District, will leave this month to take over as superintendent of the growing 
Yucaipa Joint Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
Yucaipa school board members chose Bennett from among 85 applicants, board 
president Jan Mishodek said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"He's very sincere and shows a real compassion for children," she said. "That's 
important in a school district such as ours." 
</P>
<P>
The Yucaipa school district, which straddles the border between San Bernardino 
and Riverside counties east of Redlands, has a growing number of minority 
students who have special educational needs, she said. Bennett, 47, impressed 
board members with his commitment to providing a good education for all 
students, she said. 
</P>
<P>
As superintendent, Bennett will oversee a staff of about 550 and an annual 
budget of about $25 million. 
</P>
<P>
Replacing Bennett in his Fullerton post will be Ronald Cooper, who is the 
district's assistant superintendent for personnel services. Cooper's position 
has yet to be filled. TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
