<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH BOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Times handicapper Bob Mieszerski lost $48 when his two horses in his $6 triple, 
Native Westerner and Hitchcock Woods, both ran out of the money in the eighth 
race after Sassy Slew, one of his picks in the seventh, won at $8. Bob, who 
started the meeting with hypothetical $1,000 bankroll, is now at $152. 
</P>
<P>
Bob's bet today is $50 to win on Girl Of France in the eighth race. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Bankroll $200 
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Loss $48 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $152 
</P>
</TEXT>
