<P>
NORTH KOREA WARNS GORBACHEV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Communist North Korea, which counts the Soviet Union among its few allies, 
today warned Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev of the "serious political 
consequences" if he goes ahead and meets Monday with South Korean President Roh 
Tae Woo in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting between Gorbachev and Roh, arranged by the United States to follow 
Gorbachev's summit talks with President Bush, was seen as a major political 
setback for North Korea. 
</P>
<P>
A North Korean Foreign Ministry spokesman said North Korea still hopes the 
meeting will not occur. 
</P>
