<P>
RON POLK PAN AM GAMES COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OMAHA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ron Polk, head coach at Mississippi State, was named today by the United States 
Baseball Federation as head coach of the USA baseball team for the 1991 Pan 
American Games in Havana. 
</P>
<P>
The team of American players will try to earn a spot in the 1992 Olympics in 
Barcelona, Spain, by finishing as one of the top qualifiers in the Pan Am 
Games. 
</P>
<P>
USBF officials said it is expected that a team needs to finish in the top four 
of the Pan Am Games to earn a berth in the 1992 Olympics. Team USA did not earn 
an automatic spot despite its 1988 Olympic gold medal in the Seoul Games. 
</P>
<P>
Polk served as an assistant coach to Stanford Coach Mark Marquess on that 
Olympic team. Both coaches also qualified teams for the 1990 College World 
Series beginning today in Omaha. 
</P>
