<P>
CELTICS TO APPROACH KRZYZEWSKI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Boston Celtics reportedly will talk with Duke University Coach Mike 
Krzyzewski about coaching the National Basketball Assn. team next season. 
</P>
<P>
Krzyzewski will meet next week with Dave Gavitt, the Celtics newly appointed 
chief operating officer, The Boston Globe today said it was told by 
unidentified sources. 
</P>
<P>
The Boston Herald today said Krzyzewski, a friend of Gavitt, has said he would 
be interested in the job if the Celtics approached him. 
</P>
<P>
The two already have had contact, Duke Athletic Director Tom Butters told the 
Globe. 
</P>
<P>
When asked about Krzyzewski, Gavitt said it is not fair to comment on 
individual candidates. 
</P>
<P>
The Celtics fired head Coach Jimmy Rodgers right after the team was eliminated 
from the playoffs by the New York Knicks. 
</P>
<P>
Boston assistant Coach Chris Ford has been mentioned as a candidate for the 
head coaching job. 
</P>
</TEXT>
